memberdef.name: ALGORITHM_REGISTRAR_DECLARATION
memberdef.initializer: virtual std::string getName() { return #NAME; } \ static AlgorithmRegistrar<NAME> registrar_

briefdescription.para: Auxiliary macro declaring the algorithm registrar for the algorithm type of the given name. This macro is to be used in the algorith declaration within the .hpp file. Note that name is a symbol name not a string.

Auxiliary macro defining the algorithm registrar for the algorithm type of the given name. This macro is to be used in the algorithm definition within the .cxx file. Note that name is a symbol name not a string.

memberdef.name: DEFINE_ALGORITHM_HEADER
memberdef.initializer: class NAME: public Algorithm { \ public: \ ALGORITHM_REGISTRAR_DECLARATION(NAME); \ NAME(std::vector<Argument> const &argumentList) \ : Algorithm(argumentList) {} \ ~NAME(){} \ virtual void run(); \ __VA_ARGS__ \ }
